# Imperative programming
Programming languages are used to write programs of various sorts. Programs are essentially a way to ask a computer to do stuff. There are, however, several ways in which it can be done!
The most widely used is called imperative programming.

As the naming implies it's essentially giving the computer the exact steps it has to do to achieve the desired goal.

# The idea behind coding
Programming languages are similar to those we're used to in real life in a way. They're essentially used as tools for communicating ideas, but with a computer. Just like you can express in English, Spanish, or Polish and the meaning can stay the same, you can express the same ideas using different programming languages.

